def nodeCast(*args, **kwargs):
    """
    Given two nodes, a source node of type A and a target node of type B, where type A is either type B or a sub-type of B,
    this command will replace the target node with the source node. That is, all node connections, DAG hierarchy and
    attribute values on the target node will be removed from the target node and placed on the source node. This operation
    will fail if either object is referenced, locked or if the nodes do not share a common sub-type. This operation is
    atomic. If the given parameters fail, then the source and target nodes will remain in their initial state prior to
    execution of the command. IMPORTANT: the command will currently ignore instance connections and instance objects.  It
    will also ignore reference nodes.
    
    .. rubric:: Flags:
    
    +--+---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------------------+-------------------------------+
    | Long Name / Short Name                                                                               | Argument Types                | Properties                    |
    +==+===================================================================================================+===============================+===============================+
    | ``copyDynamicAttrs`` / ``cda``                                                                       | *bool*                        | .. image:: /images/create.gif |
    +--+---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------------------+-------------------------------+
    |  | If the target node contains any dynamic attributes that are not defined on the source node, then create identical dynamic attricutes on the source node and copy  |
    |  | the values and connections from the target node into them.                                       Flag can have multiple arguments, passed either as a tuple or a  |
    |  | list.                                                                                                                                                             |
    +--+---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------------------+-------------------------------+
    | ``disableAPICallbacks`` / ``dsa``                                                                    | *bool*                        | .. image:: /images/create.gif |
    +--+---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------------------+-------------------------------+
    |  | add comment                                                                                                                                                       |
    +--+---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------------------+-------------------------------+
    | ``disableScriptJobCallbacks`` / ``dsj``                                                              | *bool*                        | .. image:: /images/create.gif |
    +--+---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------------------+-------------------------------+
    |  | add comment                                                                                                                                                       |
    +--+---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------------------+-------------------------------+
    | ``disconnectUnmatchedAttrs`` / ``dua``                                                               | *bool*                        | .. image:: /images/create.gif |
    +--+---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------------------+-------------------------------+
    |  | If the node that is being swapped out has any connections that do not exist on the target node, then indicate if the connection should be disconnected. By default|
    |  | these connections are not removed because they cannot be restored if the target node is swapped back with the source node.                                        |
    +--+---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------------------+-------------------------------+
    | ``force`` / ``f``                                                                                    | *bool*                        | .. image:: /images/create.gif |
    +--+---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------------------+-------------------------------+
    |  | Forces the command to do the node cast operation even if the nodes do not share a common base object. When this flag is specified the command will try to do the  |
    |  | best possible attribute matching when swapping the command.  It is notrecommended to use the '-swapValues/sv' flag with this flag.                                |
    +--+---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------------------+-------------------------------+
    | ``swapNames`` / ``sn``                                                                               | *bool*                        | .. image:: /images/create.gif |
    +--+---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------------------+-------------------------------+
    |  | Swap the names of the nodes. By default names are not swapped.                                                                                                    |
    +--+---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------------------+-------------------------------+
    | ``swapValues`` / ``sv``                                                                              | *bool*                        | .. image:: /images/create.gif |
    +--+---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------------------+-------------------------------+
    |  | Indicates if the commands should exchange attributes on the common attributes between the two nodes.  For example, if the nodes are the same base type as a       |
    |  | transform node, then rotate, scale, translate values would be copied over.                                                                                        |
    +--+---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+-------------------------------+-------------------------------+
    
    Derived from mel command `maya.cmds.nodeCast`
    
    
    .. rubric:: Example:
    
    ::
        
        
        import pymel.core as pm
        
        tr1 = pm.createNode( 'transform' )
        tr2 = pm.createNode( 'transform' )
        pm.connectAttr( tr1 + ".t", tr2 + ".t" )
        pm.connectAttr( tr2 + ".r", tr1 + ".r" )
        theT = tr1
        pm.select( theT, replace=1 )
        pm.addAttr( ln="unmatched", at="long" )
        middle_man = pm.createNode( 'transform' )
        pm.connectAttr( theT + ".unmatched", middle_man + ".tx" )
        swapNode = pm.createNode( 'transform' )
        pm.nodeCast( theT, swapNode, disconnectUnmatchedAttrs=true )
    """

